Create a custom exception class, for example, InsufficientFundsException.
Write a program simulating a bank account withdrawal where you throw this custom exception if the withdrawal amount exceeds the balance.
Handle this exception in the calling code.



OUTPUT:-
Transaction successful
Amount of Rs.700.0 is more than your A/c balance!
A/c Balance: 500.0



class InsufficientFundsException extends Exception{
    public InsufficientFundsException(String message){
        super(message);
    }
}

class BankAccount{
    public double balance;
    public BankAccount(double balance){
        this.balance = balance;
    }
    public void withdraw(double amount) throws InsufficientFundsException{
        if(amount > balance){
            throw new InsufficientFundsException("Amount of Rs."+amount+" is more than your A/c balance!");
        }
        else{
            balance = balance - amount;
            System.out.println("Transaction successful");
        }
    }
}

public class App{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        BankAccount b = new BankAccount(1000);
        try{
            b.withdraw(500);
            b.withdraw(700);
        }
        catch(InsufficientFundsException e){
            System.out.println(e.getMessage());
        }
        finally{
            System.out.println("A/c Balance: "+ b.balance);
        }
    }
}    
